<font color="#FF0000">GUILTY</font><br>
<tt>Sun May 25  9:27:19 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I did not go and I have been suffering about it ever since. I enlisted USMC May 1968 completed ITR and Comm school in San Diego in August, and got sent to Court House Bay at Lejune. What a miserable place. Got called for Language school in Monterey and studied Vietnamese for 47 weeks. Finished school  and was sent to Pendleton, comm repair at Las Pulgas, and left the service a year later with an itch for the last 30 years. I got exposed to agent orange while repairing PRC 25's in the shop. Can you believe it. What I believe is that many of my best friends in life died in that war and I was not there with them. I know many would say you should feel grateful for not going, but I feel guilty and cry about it-like now.I have respect for all who served during Vietnam and especially those friends who died. I guess my bitte pill is to never forget them and to wonder why I was so lucky.
<p><code>-- dwa@dwa.net  (Ernest K. Jones, Jr.) </code><p>


